        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:51PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 151 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles south of Grover, or 36 miles northeast of Greeley, moving
southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grover, Keota, New Raymer and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
